   <head>To Respectiue Readers.</head>
   <l>GAllants expect no idle newes,</l>
   <l>For carrying tales I scorne to vse,</l>
   <l>Imploy their tongues that way who will,</l>
   <l>Mens heads with strange reports to fill,</l>
   <l>Of what is done in forraigne lands</l>
   <l>I cleer from those things wash my hands,</l>
   <l>I meddle not like light-brain'd men,</l>
   <l>VVith this and that, and where &amp; when,</l>
   <l>And how and which and what and why,</l>
   <l>And thus, and so, I scorne it I,</l>
   <l>I haue a melancholy Scull</l>
   <l>Is almost fractur'd tis so full</l>
   <l>To ease the same these lines I write,</l>
   <l>Tobacco boy a pipe, some light.</l>
</div>
